'''''Oxford Handbook of Japanese Cinema''''' is a 2010 [[non-fiction book]] published by [[Oxford University Press]] and edited by [[Daisuke Miyao]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Sharp|first1=Jasper|title=The Oxford Handbook of Japanese Cinema|journal=The Times Literary Supplement|date=August 2014|page=38|location=London}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Amit|first1=Rea|title=HomeBook Reviews Rewriting Japanese Cinema for the Global Age: The Oxford Handbook of Japanese Cinema by Daisuke Miyao (ed.)|url=http://sensesofcinema.com/2014/book-reviews/rewriting-japanese-cinema-for-the-global-age-the-oxford-handbook-of-japanese-cinema-by-daisuke-miyao-ed/|issue=73|accessdate=3 March 2015|work=Sense of Cinema|date=December 2014}}</ref><ref name="Wroot2015">{{cite journal|last1=Wroot|first1=Jonathan|title=The Oxford Handbook of Japanese Cinema, edited by Daisuke Miyao / East Asian Film Stars, edited by Leung Wing-Fai and Andy Willis|journal=Journal of Japanese and Korean Cinema|volume=7|issue=2|year=2015|pages=167–170|issn=1756-4905|doi=10.1080/17564905.2015.1087155}}</ref>

